SIMPLE: parricide
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parricide
<hw>Par"ri*cide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>parricida</ets>; <ets>pater</ets> father + <ets>caedere</ets> to
kill. See <er>Father</er>, <er>Homicide</er>, and cf.
<er>Patricide</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Properly, one who murders one's own father; in a
wider sense, one who murders one's father or mother or any
ancestor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[L. <ets>parricidium</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act or
crime of murdering one's own father or any ancestor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parricidious</ent>⟦br⟧
